Supervisor --> ProcRef : "manages"
EventManager --> Proc : "notifies"
ProcMonitor --> Proc : "observes"
ProcLink --> Proc : "links"
ProcRegistry --> Proc : "stores"
ProcTimer --> Proc : "messages"
ProcLib --> Proc : "initializes"
ProcSys --> Proc : "introspects"
CrashRecovery --> Result : "wraps"
Parallel --> Proc : "coordinates"
StateMachine --> Proc : "state logic"

'' Tier 0.5 relationships
GenServer_1 --> Proc : "wraps"
GenServer_1 --> Result : "returns"
PoolSupervisor_1 --> Supervisor : "supervises"
PoolSupervisor_1 --> ProcRegistry : "discovers"
Application_1 --> GenServer_1 : "orchestrates"
Application_1 --> PoolSupervisor_1 : "manages"
Application_1 --> Supervisor : "coordinates"

'' Tier 1 relationships
Behavior --> GenServer_1 : "replaces pattern matching"
RetryPolicy --> CrashRecovery : "wraps"
RetryPolicy --> Result : "returns"
CircuitBreaker --> Supplier : "wraps"
CircuitBreaker --> StateMachine : "state machine"
BackpressureQueue --> Proc : "bounds"
HealthCheck --> ProcSys : "augments statistics"

'' Tier 2 relationships
RateLimiter --> Parallel : "throttles"
RequestContext --> Proc : "context in handlers"
ChannelBuffer --> Proc : "async messaging"
SupervisorBuilder --> Supervisor : "builds"
Metrics --> ProcSys : "extends statistics"

'' Tier 3 relationships
GenServerBehavior --> Behavior : "extends"
Saga --> Application_1 : "coordinates"
DistributedRegistry --> ProcRegistry : "extends"
TransactionLog --> EventManager : "logs events"

note right of Behavior
    Callback-based alternative to pattern matching
    Users who prefer OOP style over sealed types
    Adapts internally to GenServer<S,M>
end note

note right of RetryPolicy
    Essential for production resilience
    Exponential backoff + jitter (prevents thundering herd)
    Works with CircuitBreaker for comprehensive fault tolerance
end note

note right of CircuitBreaker
    CLOSED→OPEN→HALF_OPEN→CLOSED state machine
    Prevents cascading failures
    Auto-recovery after timeout or success threshold
end note

note right of BackpressureQueue
    Prevents unbounded queue growth → OOM
    Alternative mailbox implementation
    Drop-oldest or reject policies
end note

note right of HealthCheck
    Proactive system monitoring
    Integrates with ProcSys for observability
    Sealed Status prevents invalid states
end note

note right of RateLimiter
    Token bucket algorithm
    Blocking and non-blocking variants
    Essential for API protection
end note

note right of RequestContext
    Java 21+ ScopedValue wrapper
    Vthread-safe (no ThreadLocal)
    Context propagation across virtual threads
end note

note right of ChannelBuffer
    Go-style channels for familiar interface
    FIFO queue with backpressure
    Alternative to ask()/tell() messaging
end note

note right of SupervisorBuilder
    Fluent API for supervisor construction
    Reduces boilerplate vs manual setup
    Enables cleaner configuration
end note

note right of Metrics
    Counter, Gauge, Histogram, Timer
    Mirroring Erlang prometheus.erl
    Integrates with ProcSys.statistics()
end note

